-- North Sea Foinaven Crude Exports to Drop to One Cargo in August
-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-07-11T15:11:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/north-sea-foinaven-crude-exports-to-drop-to-one-cargo-in-august.html
Exports of North Sea Foinaven crude
will drop to one 350,000-barrel cargo for August, compared with
two shipments of 600,000 barrels each in July, according to a
loading schedule obtained by Bloomberg News.  BP Plc (BP/)  operates the offshore U.K. field. Loading programs
are monthly schedules of crude shipments compiled by field
operators to allow buyers and sellers to plan their supply and
trading activities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sherry Su in London at 
 lsu23@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
